Historical Chart Gallery
Key Market Indexes






                        These charts show long-term historical trends for commonly followed US market indexes. These charts are updated every Friday evening.
                        Members can click on these charts to see live versions - PRO members will see complete versions while other members will only see data from 1980 until now.

The chart includes monthly price data, trading volumes, and key metrics: opening, high, low, and closing values, with the latest close at $2,681.00 on November 29, 2024.

A historical line chart displaying the U.S. unemployment rate from 1940 to 2024, showing cyclical peaks during periods of economic downturns, such as the early 1980s and the late 2000s. The latest data, as of October 1, 2024, indicates an unemployment rate of 4.10%. The chart provides monthly data, illustrating fluctuations in the labor market over time.

Notable growth occurs post-1980s, leading to a recent close at 6,032.38. The chart includes monthly data with key metrics: opening, high, low, closing values, and trading volume.

A historical line chart of the Consumer Price Index (CPI), seasonally adjusted, from 1945 to October 1, 2024. It shows a consistent long-term upward trend, reflecting inflation over time, with the latest close at 315.45. The chart includes monthly data and key metrics: opening, high, low, and closing values.

A historical line chart showing the Silver Spot Price from 1970 to November 29, 2024, highlighting significant volatility with peaks in the early 1980s and post-2008. The chart displays fluctuations in silver prices, with the most recent close at 31.11. Included are monthly data points with key metrics: opening, high, low, closing values, and trading volume.

The chart highlights significant growth since the mid-20th century, leading to a recent close of 20,272.04. It includes monthly data with key metrics: opening, high, low, closing values, and trading volume.

A historical line chart of the Dow Jones Utility Average (UTIL) from 1928 to November 29, 2024, showing a long-term upward trend with periods of volatility. Significant fluctuations are observed mid-century, with a steady rise in recent decades, culminating in a close of 1,078.95. The chart includes monthly data with key metrics: opening, high, low, closing values, and trading volume.
